President Obama spoke with Yukio Hatoyama, the President of the Democratic Party of Japan, to congratulate him on the results of the Lower House elections. They both emphasized the importance of a strong U.S.-Japan alliance and expressed their desire to build a more effective partnership. President Obama expressed his wish to work with Mr. Hatoyama and the Japanese government on various issues, including global economic recovery, climate change, denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula, combating extremism in Afghanistan, and promoting peace and prosperity in the Asia-Pacific region. They also planned to meet during the United Nations General Assembly and the G-20 Summit later that month.